AN off-duty Joburg Metro police department and South African Police Services officer have been arrested.They were bust for discharging their departmental firearms in an apparent attempt to protect their mother. It happened in Eldorado Park, south of Joburg, authorities said yesterday. The JMPD officer discharged his firearm on Saturday night when a crowd of people allegedly gathered to attack his mother&rsquo;s house and damage his car, Metro chief Superintendent Wayne Minnaar said this followed an argument between his mother and a neighbour.He said it was also alleged that the officer&rsquo;s brother, who is a member of the SAPS, was arrested for having shot and killed a person. That shooting is believed to have arisen from the same situation. &ldquo;The JMPD officer will be investigated internally for having used a service pistol while he was off-duty,&rdquo; Minnaar said. Police could not immediately be reached for comment. &ndash; NEWS24